===Etymology===
{{etyl|ang}} {{term|gat|gāt|lang=ang}}, from {{proto|Germanic|gaits}} (compare {{etyl|nl|-}} {{term|geit|lang=nl}}, {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|Geiß|lang=de}}, Danish {{term|ged|lang=de}}), from {{proto|Indo-European|gʰaid-|lang=}} 'kid, goat' (compare {{etyl|la}} {{term|haedus||lang=la}} 'kid', {{etyl|cu|-}} {{term|заѩць|tr=zajęcĭ|lang=cu}} 'hare', {{etyl|hy|-}} {{term|ձի|tr=ji|lang=hy}} 'horse', {{etyl|sa|-}} {{term|हय|tr=háya|lang=sa}} 'horse', {{term|जिहीते|tr=jihīte|lang=sa}} 'he jumps').

